i use dubbo 2.7.5

ServletHttpBind class info：

public class ServletHttpBinder implements HttpBinder {

    @Override
    @Adaptive()
    public HttpServer bind(URL url, HttpHandler handler) {
        return new ServletHttpServer(url, handler);
    }

}

I analyzed JettyHttpBinder and TomcatHttpBinder and found that ServletHttpBinder is using this servlet request. In other words, if a service is deployed on the server, then a request is initiated, and then it is performed in a servlet container.
deal with. The Adaptive annotation here has no effect on the implementation of the function, so it is recommended to remove this annotation on the method.

modify：

public class ServletHttpBinder implements HttpBinder {

    @Override
    public HttpServer bind(URL url, HttpHandler handler) {
        return new ServletHttpServer(url, handler);
    }

}

